{
  "deltas": [
    {"dt": 0, "type": "text", "text": "Metallic-Oxide-Semiconductor Field-Effect Transistors (MOSFETs) control a current between the source (down) and drain (up) by applying a voltage to the gate (left)."},
    {"dt": 2, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "PNP", "type": "pmosfet", "position": {"x": 180, "y": 20}, "orient": 0}},
    {"dt": 0, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "NPN", "type": "nmosfet", "position": {"x": 20, "y": 20}, "orient": 0}},
    {"dt": 3, "type": "text", "text": "We will primarily discuss the N-channel version, since the P-channel version is less efficient and is generally the inverse of the P-channel."},
    {"dt": 1, "type": "delComponent", "id": "PNP"},
    {"dt": 3, "type": "text", "text": "Generally, where a BJT transistor relies on current, a MOSFET relies on voltage."},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "connection", "conn": {"type": "v", "x": 20, "sy": 100, "ey": 140}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "V-", "type": "vpin", "value": 0, "position": {"x": 20, "y": 140}, "orient": 0}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "connection", "conn": {"type": "h", "y": 140, "sx": 20, "ex": 180}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "G1", "type": "ground", "position": {"x": 180, "y": 180}, "orient": 0}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "connection", "conn": {"type": "v", "x": 180, "sy": 60, "ey": 140}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "V1", "type": "voltage", "value": 5, "position": {"x": 180, "y": 20}, "orient": 3}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "connection", "conn": {"type": "v", "x": 180, "sy": -60, "ey": -20}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "connection", "conn": {"type": "h", "y": -60, "sx": 140, "ex": 180}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "R", "type": "resistor", "value": 100, "position": {"x": 100, "y": -60}, "orient": 0}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "IR", "tetherId": "R", "type": "clabel",  "value": 0, "position": {"x": 100, "y": -40}, "orient": 0}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "connection", "conn": {"type": "h", "y": -60, "sx": 20, "ex": 60}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "V+", "type": "vpin", "value": 5, "position": {"x": 20, "y": -60}, "orient": 0}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "connection", "conn": {"type": "v", "x": 20, "sy": -60, "ey": -20}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "Vb", "type": "vpin", "value": 0, "position": {"x": -60, "y": 60}, "orient": 0}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "connection", "conn": {"type": "h", "y": 60, "sx": -100, "ex": -60}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "S", "type": "spdt", "value": 0, "position": {"x": -140, "y": 60}, "orient": 2}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "connection", "conn": {"type": "h", "y": 100, "sx": -220, "ex": -180}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "G2", "type": "ground", "position": {"x": -220, "y": 140}, "orient": 0}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "component", "element": {"id": "V2", "type": "voltage", "value": 5, "position": {"x": -220, "y": 60}, "orient": 3}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "connection", "conn": {"type": "h", "y": 20, "sx": -220, "ex": -180}},
    {"dt": 0.1, "type": "text", "text": "The N-channel MOSFET shorts the drain-source connection when the voltage difference between the gate and source is high (5V, in this example)."},
    {"dt": 4, "type": "text", "text": "Since there is insufficient voltage difference between the gate and source, the transistor currently acts as an open circuit."},
    {"dt": 4, "type": "text", "text": "When we flip the switch, there is a sufficient voltage difference between the gate and source..."},
    {"dt": 1, "type": "modifyValue", "id": "S", "value": 1},
    {"dt": 0, "type": "modifyValue", "id": "Vb", "value": 5},
    {"dt": 0, "type": "modifyValue", "id": "V+", "value": 0},
    {"dt": 0, "type": "modifyValue", "id": "IR", "value": -0.05},
    {"dt": 4, "type": "text", "text": "...so the transistor will act like a short circuit from source to drain. [END]"}
  ]
}